\c 22
\s1 103. Wanbala men
\s2 Jarrinyiyi lilmi jir-neni wubirr
\p ▫
\q1 Jarrinyiyi lilmi jir-neni wubirr,
\q1 Bili-nyunenu rugalarra wamam.
\q1 Nurligi1 bili-nyunenu wirdiga,
\q1 Binjurr niba dewu-mayi ,alawal barab-mayin.
\q1 Ninda gulurr yirrwarrini gulurr alawal gereng-mayin,
\q1 Diyanga niba yirrwarrini diyanga wulegi wubu.
\q1 Ga-nemberli wulegi marraman
\q1 Guruguru niba alawal gereng-mayin wulegi wunarru.
\b
\q1 Nurligi* namumban “Guda ngayi yagul-yirni.
\q1 Ngina banga ngina nga-bing-garrarnu.
\q1 Waynma, ngina nga-waynma.
\q1 Jangarl-ngayiman, durn-ngayiman, guda nga-waynma.
\q1 Ngina nga-yiligarri, ngina nga-yiligarri balgayi.
\q1 Ngayi nyingaya-ngarni nyamba jangarl-nyiyi
\q1 Ngina-nda nga-yiligarri waynmayi.”
\q1 Ninda lilmi, Jisas Krais, malmal Godja.
\b
\qr Words translated from Kriol Rebaleishan 1.13-18 by Minyerri mob. Tune: Majesty. @ Frankdon Music Pty Ltd. Crows Nest, N.S.W.
\qr *Words supplied jarrinyiyi lilmi but nurligi better, meaning “that same man”
\c 23
\s1 120. Stakmen bin maindim ola ship
\s2 Yilstakmen yilmabanna nanigut
\p ▫
\q1 Yilstakmen yilmabanna nanigut
\q1 Wulamburr Betlehem
\q1 Maruwarr jum-nayiman Godjiyunu
\q1 Girri! Yagul-yili.
\b
\q1 Namumban yilunga “Ngayi yagul-yilni
\q1 Yumarr-da nanggaya ngaba.
\q1 Wunya durd-namban-da malmal
\q1 Barda yiligarri wulunga narni.”
\b
\q1 Nurligirri maruwarra namban yilunga,
\q1 “Dali gada ngemberli wulunga.
\q1 Wulinya dul-wulangana-da malmal
\q1 Yarna-nyi buligirr yadji.”
\b
\q1 Yilmaruwarr yilwuyga yilaja-gunu guda,
\q1 Warr-yilanna “God yamirni.
\q1 Nurla yamirni wulanga, yumarr wulunga,
\q1 Yumarr nyurranji.”
\b
\q1 Yiliman yilmaruwarr, yillilmi yilmumban,
\q1 “Nyulinya guyn-nyularnu-da malmal.”
\q1 Yiliman yadjirru guyn-jilanna wulagi
\q1 Ngarl-yinbirranya.
\b
\qr Words by Margaret Sharpe and Barney Farrar. Tune: While shepherds watched their flocks by night.
